The paper focuses on developing a machine learning-based system for detecting software vulnerabilities in source code. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR) categories. The use of deep feature representation learning also suggests a potential overlap with the machine learning (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of static analyzers, which could indicate a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well.
